-- Benin Needs to Follow `Prudent' Budget Policy to Post Surplus, IMF Says
-- B y   V e r n o n   W e s s e l s
-- 2010-10-05T05:09:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-05/benin-needs-to-follow-prudent-budget-policy-to-post-surplus-imf-says.html
Benin should follow a prudent budget
policy for the rest of its fiscal year and 2011 in an effort to
achieve a “small basic primary budget” next year, the
International Monetary Fund said in a statement on its website,
dated yesterday.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
